==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lower-case
<hw>Low"er-case`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or kept in, the
lower case; -- used to denote the small letters, in distinction from
capitals and small capitals; <as>as, <ex>lowercase</ex> letters a and b
and c etc.</as>. Contrasted with <ant>uppercase</ant>. See the Note
under 1st <er>Case</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lower-class</ent>⟦br⟧
